23 neque here means simply non, a sense which neque and nec so often had in archaic Latin, and which is not uncommon in classical: so v1 1214 neque se possent cognoscere ut ipsi, 111 730 At neque cur faciant ipsae quareve laborent Dicere suppeditat : so lv 1217 neque utrum: see n. there: and v 839 nec utrum.
